{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Give all UK citizens the right to a non-binding vote on parliamentary debates.",
        "additional_details": "This is a crude solution to the issue of representative democracy versus direct democracy in the UK. \r\n\r\nMany citizens feel as though a vote on who should represent them in parliament every five years isn\u2019t democratic enough.\r\n\r\nIf you think the proposed system\r\nis better than the current system, sign this petition.",
        "background": "Citizens already have the right to view almost all parliamentary debates online. \r\n\r\nAdd a simple voting mechanism for the public to vote.\r\n\r\nBuild digital infrastructure on parliament.uk which allows those with UK citizenship a non-binding vote (\u2018aye\u2019/\u2018no\u2019/abstain) on all debates in parliament.",
